          <section id="benefits">
               <h2>Benefits of Healthy Nutrition</h2>
               <p>Eating a healthy and balanced diet has numerous benefits, including:</p>
               <ul>
                    <li>Reduced risk of chronic diseases like heart disease, diabetes, and cancer</li>
                    <li>Improved cognitive function and mental health</li>
                    <li>Increase in energy and overall well-being</li>
                    <li>Maintaining a healthy weight</li>
               </ul>
          </section>
          <section id="food-groups">
               <h2>Food Groups</h2>
               <p>A healthy diet includes a variety of foods from each of the following food groups:</p>
               <ul>
                    <li>Vegetables and fruits</li>
                    <li>Grains and cereals</li>
                    <li>Proteins (meat, fish, beans, nuts, and seeds)</li>
                    <li>Dairy or dairy alternatives</li>
               </ul>
               <p>It's important to choose whole, minimally processed foods and limit your intake of sugary and fatty foods.</p>
          </section>
          <section id="meal-planning">
               <h2>Meal Planning</h2>
               <p>Planning your meals ahead of time can help you make healthier food choices and stick to a balanced diet. Some tips for meal planning include:</p>
               <ul>
                    <li>Creating a grocery list based on your planned meals</li>
                    <li>Preparing meals in advance and storing them in the fridge or freezer</li>
                    <li>Choosing recipes that incorporate a variety of healthy ingredients</li>
               </ul>
               <p>Remember to listen to your body's hunger and fullness signals, and aim for a balanced plate with a variety of foods.</p>
          </section>
